---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Digital Marketing for SaaS Companies" description="B2B SaaS marketing that drives demos, trials, and qualified leads. PPC, content-led SEO, and LinkedIn targeting from Spires Digital.">
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Industries', href: '/industries/saas' }, { label: 'SaaS' }]} />

  <section class="page-hero" style="margin-top: -2rem;">
    <div class="container page-hero-content">
      <span class="badge">SaaS Marketing</span>
      <h1>Digital Marketing for SaaS Companies</h1>
      <p>Pipeline-focused campaigns that generate qualified leads, demo bookings, and trial sign-ups. We help B2B SaaS companies scale acquisition while reducing cost per lead.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Challenge -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>The SaaS Marketing Challenge</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 2rem;">SaaS growth demands a different playbook. Long sales cycles, multiple stakeholders, and fierce competition make customer acquisition uniquely complex.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <div class="challenge-card">
          <div class="icon-box">💰</div>
          <h3>High Customer Acquisition Costs</h3>
          <p>B2B keywords are expensive, and long sales cycles mean you're paying for leads months before they convert. Without precise targeting, CAC spirals out of control.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="challenge-card">
          <div class="icon-box">🎯</div>
          <h3>Reaching Decision-Makers</h3>
          <p>Your ideal customer isn't casually browsing — they're researching solutions during specific buying windows. Timing and targeting precision are everything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="challenge-card">
          <div class="icon-box">📈</div>
          <h3>Proving Marketing ROI</h3>
          <p>With long sales cycles spanning weeks or months, connecting marketing spend to closed revenue requires proper attribution and pipeline tracking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="challenge-card">
          <div class="icon-box">🏆</div>
          <h3>Standing Out in Crowded Markets</h3>
          <p>Every SaaS category is saturated with competitors. Generic messaging gets ignored — you need positioning that resonates with your specific ICP.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Our Approach -->
      <h2>Our Approach to SaaS Growth</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 2rem;">We combine paid acquisition with content-led SEO to build a predictable, scalable pipeline for your SaaS product.</p>
      <div class="process-steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3>ICP &amp; Funnel Mapping</h3>
            <p>We define your ideal customer profile, map the buyer journey, and identify the highest-intent touchpoints where marketing drives the most pipeline value.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Paid Acquisition Strategy</h3>
            <p>Google Ads for high-intent search queries, LinkedIn for precise B2B targeting, and Meta for awareness and retargeting — each channel assigned a clear role in the funnel.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Content-Led SEO</h3>
            <p>Bottom-of-funnel comparison pages, feature-focused landing pages, and thought leadership content that builds organic authority and captures search demand over time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Optimise to Pipeline</h3>
            <p>We don't optimise to vanity metrics. Campaigns are measured against qualified leads, demo bookings, and ultimately closed revenue.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> SaaS companies that combine Google Ads for high-intent search with LinkedIn for account-based targeting typically see 40–60% lower cost per qualified lead compared to single-channel strategies.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services for SaaS -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt);">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>Services for SaaS Companies</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Our services are adapted to the unique demands of B2B SaaS customer acquisition.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <a href="/services/ppc-management" class="service-link-card">
          <h3>PPC for SaaS</h3>
          <p>High-intent Google Ads campaigns targeting buyers actively searching for solutions like yours. Smart bidding optimised to demo bookings, not just clicks.</p>
          <span class="link-arrow">Learn more →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/meta-ads" class="service-link-card">
          <h3>Meta &amp; LinkedIn Ads</h3>
          <p>Targeted social campaigns to reach decision-makers by job title, company size, and industry. Ideal for awareness, retargeting, and account-based strategies.</p>
          <span class="link-arrow">Learn more →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats / Results -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2 style="text-align: center;">Results We Deliver for SaaS</h2>
      <p style="text-align: center; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Average performance improvements across our SaaS client portfolio.</p>
      <div class="stat-grid">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">+145%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Qualified Lead Volume</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">-52%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Cost Per Acquisition</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">+210%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Organic Traffic Growth</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">3.2×</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Demo Booking Rate</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt);">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you work with early-stage SaaS or only established companies?</summary>
          <p>We work with SaaS companies at all stages. For early-stage businesses, we focus on validating channels quickly with lean budgets. For established products, we scale what's working and diversify acquisition channels to reduce dependency on any single source.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do you measure success for SaaS campaigns?</summary>
          <p>We track the metrics that matter to your business: qualified leads, demo bookings, trial sign-ups, and pipeline revenue. We work with your CRM data to connect marketing spend to actual closed deals, not just form fills.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can you help with LinkedIn advertising?</summary>
          <p>Yes — LinkedIn is a core channel for B2B SaaS. We build campaigns targeting decision-makers by job title, company size, industry, and seniority. Combined with retargeting, it's one of the most effective channels for reaching your ICP.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long does it take to see results from SEO?</summary>
          <p>SEO is a long-term investment. Most SaaS clients see meaningful organic traffic improvements within 3–6 months, with compounding returns over time. We prioritise bottom-of-funnel content first to generate pipeline as quickly as possible.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What budget do you recommend for SaaS paid acquisition?</summary>
          <p>It depends on your market and goals, but most B2B SaaS clients invest &pound;3,000–&pound;15,000 per month in paid media. We'll recommend a starting budget based on your target CPA, market competition, and growth targets.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Build a Predictable SaaS Pipeline?</h2>
      <p>Get a free strategy session to discuss how we can drive qualified demos and trials for your product.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Book Free Strategy Call</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you work with early-stage SaaS or only established companies?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "We work with SaaS companies at all stages. For early-stage businesses, we focus on validating channels quickly with lean budgets. For established products, we scale what's working and diversify acquisition channels to reduce dependency on any single source."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you measure success for SaaS campaigns?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "We track the metrics that matter to your business: qualified leads, demo bookings, trial sign-ups, and pipeline revenue. We work with your CRM data to connect marketing spend to actual closed deals, not just form fills."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you help with LinkedIn advertising?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes — LinkedIn is a core channel for B2B SaaS. We build campaigns targeting decision-makers by job title, company size, industry, and seniority. Combined with retargeting, it's one of the most effective channels for reaching your ICP."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to see results from SEO?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "SEO is a long-term investment. Most SaaS clients see meaningful organic traffic improvements within 3–6 months, with compounding returns over time. We prioritise bottom-of-funnel content first to generate pipeline as quickly as possible."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What budget do you recommend for SaaS paid acquisition?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "It depends on your market and goals, but most B2B SaaS clients invest £3,000–£15,000 per month in paid media. We'll recommend a starting budget based on your target CPA, market competition, and growth targets."
        }
      }
    ]
  })} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .challenge-card { padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius); }
  .challenge-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .challenge-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .process-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
  .step { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; align-items: start; }
  .step-num { width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-accent); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .step h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .step p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .service-link-card { display: block; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-white); border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); transition: all var(--transition); text-decoration: none; }
  .service-link-card:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg); border-color: var(--color-accent); }
  .service-link-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .service-link-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .link-arrow { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-accent); }
  .faq-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .faq-item { background: var(--color-white); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); overflow: hidden; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; margin-left: 1rem; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.7; }
</style>
